aa(lp332
VThis is what happens when we confuse morality with frugality.
p333
aVWe've all been taught that the bake sale with five percent overhead
p334
aVis morally superior to the professional fundraising enterprise
p335
aVwith 40 percent overhead,
p336
aVbut we're missing the most important piece of information, which is:
p337
aVWhat is the actual size of these pies?
p338
aVWho cares if the bake sale only has five percent overhead if it's tiny?
p339
aVWhat if the bake sale only netted 71 dollars for charity
p340
aVbecause it made no investment in its scale
p341
aVand the professional fundraising enterprise netted
p342
aV71 million dollars because it did?
